text: Middlesex County is a rural county in Southwestern Ontario, Canada. According to the Canada 2021 Census, it had a population of 78,239. The county seat is in the city of London, even though London is politically independent of the county. Middlesex County has eight incorporated municipalites: Adelaide Metcalfe, Lucan Biddulph, Middlesex Centre, Newbury, North Middlesex, Southwest Middlesex, Strathroy-Caradoc, and Thames Centre. There are also three reservations of the First Nations in the county: Chippewas of the Thames 42, Munsee-Delaware 1, and Onedia 41. Category:Counties of Ontario
title: Middlesex County, Ontario
